===Etymology===
From the Old Norse ''Alvíss'', genitive of ''Alvís'' (''all-wise''), from ''al'' (''all''), + ''vís'' (''wise, knowing''), from Germanic ''*weiso'' (''sense''), from PIE ''*ueid-'' (''to look at''); + ''mál'' (''collection, speech''), from Germanic ''*maþla'' (''speech''), from PIE ''*mād-''.

===Proper noun===
'''Alvíssmál'''
# The Sayings of Alvís (''or'') The Sayings of the All-Wise; the tenth book of the [[Poetic Edda]].

